
<item rdf:about='http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-ko-vaas-problem-statement-01.txt'>
    <title>"Problem Statement for VPN As A Service", Edward Wang, Robert Raszuk</title>
    <link>http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-ko-vaas-problem-statement-01.txt</link>
    <description>This document examines the problems and challenges associated with the process of setting up secure connections between authorized network nodes.  The network nodes can be located anywhere in a private or public network, directly connected or behind one or more levels of NAT.  Setting up a secure connection in this environment entails the resolution of various issues such as authentication, peer discovery, virtual network address management, routing information exchange and connection parameters determination.</description>
    <dc:date>2011-10-27T22:00:00-00:00</dc:date>
</item>
